From 477b13bc66b0184cf64cfec6ed42a4d307b6d279 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Your Name <you@example.com>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 22:45:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] align logos-blockchain ee281a4 -> 0.1.2 (match the
 deployed L1 node)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Re-pin all logos-blockchain crates to the 0.1.2 release (commit 05f84a5), the version
the diaphani-fronted Logos node runs, so the sequencer speaks the node's block format.

The only source breakage was sequencer_core/block_publisher.rs: 0.1.2's zone-sdk
collapsed the sequencer Event model (Event -> just TxsFinalized{tx_hashes}; checkpoints
now come from publish_message's PublishResult) and drives its own loop via
ZoneSequencer::spawn(). A cross-crate manual next_event loop also trips rustc #100013
(0.1.2's adapter is async-fn-in-trait / impl Stream). Rewrote to drive via the zone-sdk's
own spawn() and take checkpoints from the publish result. Finalized-block pruning is
deferred (0.1.2 exposes no public Event subscription) - safe, since stale resubmits are
rejected as InvalidParent. TODO: restore via a subscribe() accessor or a LIB watermark.

PROVEN: the version-matched sequencer connects to the real diaphani Bedrock L1 over Tor
(diaphani-forward), syncs with NO parse errors, and produces L2 blocks + publishes
inscriptions to the channel. Branch align-logos-0.1.2.
